{% set title = '## **Gathering Preferred Date and Time** procedure' %}

{% set body %}
Your task in this procedure is to collect the user's **Event** fields:
- **Date**
- **Time**

Check the <ConversationHistory> and <UserInformation> first, and ask only about the fields that the User has not provided yet.

- If the User has mentioned a day using terms like: "today", "tomorrow", "the day after tomorrow", "the next [day of the week]", etc., use <ConvoAgentCalendar> to interpret it correctly. Always reconfirm the chosen date as follows:
"So it's on [user's preferred day of the week according to <ConvoAgentCalendar>] [user's preferred date according to <ConvoAgentCalendar>] at [user's preferred time]?"

- The User must choose a preferred time that falls within **Working hours** on their selected day, according to <WorkingSchedule>.  If the day and/or time is outside of <WorkingSchedule>, ConvoAgent must notify them and request another time: "I'm sorry, but we can only serve during our working hours. Our services are available [outline <WorkingSchedule>]."

If any of the fields are missing in the <ConversationHistory>, **you must remain on this step and collect the missing information.**
{% endset %}

{% set description %}
This procedure collects the user’s preferred Date and Time, asking only for missing details, interpreting relative days with <ConvoAgentCalendar>, and reconfirming: “Do you mean [weekday] [date] at [time]?” If time or date is unspecified, propose a reasonable business-hour slot and explicitly say, “Let me check available slots for [user's preferred day] at [user's preferred time] right now,” remaining on this step until both fields are captured.
{% endset %}

{% set item = {
    "idn": "procedure_common_gather_date_time_catering",
    "title": title.strip(),
    "body": body.strip(),
    "mentions": [],
    "description": description.strip(),
    "is_from_library": True,
    "origin_idn": ""
} %}

{{Return(val=json.dumps(item, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))}}
